#1 Ulcerated mass in the sigmoid colon worrisome for malignancy
Discussed development, staging, and treatment of colon cancer with Mr. Uy.  At this time we will proceed with staging lab work including CBC, chemistry panel, CEA, and given the sweats also check a TSH level.  He will obtain a chest x-ray and a CT abdomen and pelvis and then have him meet with Colorectal Surgery for surgical recommendations.  Patient will need to meet back with Cardiology for preoperative clearance, especially given his cardiovascular disease, history of headaches, and possible vascular disease.  Discussed plan of care with patient and answered questions.
Discussed with Dr. Hood, note to follow.

